So, I woke up this morning, scrolled through my feeds, and had a revelation: 
Social media has turned into the world's largest Ponzi scheme, but instead of money, we're all trading in followers.
Everyone's an influencer now—even my neighbors dog has an Instagram account with more followers than I do. We've built this digital Tower of Babel, trading genuine connection for a shot at internet fame that’s as fleeting as a Snapchat selfie.
